<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1897-03-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1897-03-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="221" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d221">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Sir <persName type="from">Julian
                                    Pauncefote</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Sherman</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">British
                                        Embassy</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1897-03-30"><hi rend="italic">March 30,
                                1897</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: I have been requested to
                            inquire, unofficially, whether it is the intention of the President of
                            the United States to send a special mission of congratulation on the
                            occasion of the celebration, in June next, of the sixtieth anniversary
                            of the Queen’s accession to the throne.</p>
                        <p>I should be greatly obliged if you could enable me to give Lord Salisbury
                            the information desired.</p>
                        <p>I remain, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Julian
                            Pauncefote.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>